          "raw_value": "local Galactic escape velocity computed from the potential model",
          "value": "local Galactic escape velocity",
          "source_refs": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "step-13",
      "depends_on": [
        "step-10",
        "step-11",
        "step-12"
      ],
      "step_type": "orbit_integration",
      "summary": "Backward orbit integration using a fourth-order Runge-Kutta-Fehlberg method with adaptive step size control, including Monte Carlo error propagation (1 million runs) for the four input observables (distance, radial velocity, two proper motion components) and their correlations, as well as uncertainties in solar parameters and non-zero disk height (Gaussian random offsets).",
      "source_refs": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "path": "literature/2101.10878/arxiv_source/paper.tex",
          "start_line": 159,
          "end_line": 159,
          "context": "The corresponding equations of motions are numerically solved with a fourth-order Runge-Kutta-Fehlberg method with adaptive stepsize control ... Error propagation ... is handled with a Monte Carlo simulation with one million runs ..."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "step-14",
      "depends_on": [
        "step-13",
        "step-12"
      ],
      "step_type": "escape_or_bound_assessment",
      "summary": "Computation of Galactic rest-frame velocity v_Grf at current position and at plane crossing, comparison with local escape velocity v_esc, and evaluation of bound probability P_b (fraction of Monte Carlo runs bound).",
      "source_refs": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "path": "literature/2101.10878/arxiv_source/paper.tex",
          "start_line": 161,
          "end_line": 161,
          "context": "While all resulting kinematic parameters are summarized in Table 3, we focus in the following on the ejection velocities ... and galactocentric radii at plane intersection ..."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
